      "username": "KatharinaSick",
      "cooked": "<p>Hey <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=15\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>Unfortunately, this would create too much overlap with the February adventure that is coming next month. Sorry!</p>\n<p>But in theory, you should be able to run the challenge locally as GitHub Codespaces are just <a href=\"https://containers.dev/\">devcontainers</a> in the end. Also, the deadline just means that no points will be rewarded afterwards. You can always play all past challenges for learning.</p>\n<p>I created a GitHub issue to take a look at local execution as well: <a href=\"https://github.com/dynatrace-oss/open-ecosystem-challenges/issues/14\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Test &amp; document local execution · Issue #14 · dynatrace-oss/open-ecosystem-challenges · GitHub</a></p>",
